---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="API Documentation - Pasteriser">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">API Documentation</h1>
    
    <div class="rounded-lg border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col space-y-1.5 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight">Introduction</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 pt-0">
        <p class="mb-4">
          The Pasteriser API allows you to programmatically create, retrieve, and manage pastes. 
          All API endpoints return JSON responses and use standard HTTP status codes.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The base URL for all API requests is:
        </p>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
          https://pasteriser.com/api/v1
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="rounded-lg border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col space-y-1.5 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight">Endpoints</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 pt-0">
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Create a Paste</h4>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
          POST /api/v1/pastes
        </div>
        
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-8">Get a Paste</h4>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
          GET /api/v1/pastes/:id
        </div>
        
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-8">Delete a Paste</h4>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-md p-3 font-mono text-sm mb-4 overflow-x-auto">
          DELETE /api/v1/pastes/:id
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="rounded-lg border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm">
      <div class="flex flex-col space-y-1.5 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-none tracking-tight">Webhooks</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 pt-0">
        <p class="mb-4">
          Pasteriser can send webhook notifications for various events. To configure webhooks, 
          please visit the <a href="/admin/webhooks" class="text-primary hover:underline">Admin Dashboard</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>